node.text:
oop, looks like my childhood called and said hey bestie ☎️👋 truly channeling my inner middle schooler today with this peanut butter and jelly sandwich 🥜🍇🍞 i didn’t even bother adultifying it (by this i mean using almond butter instead of peanut, lol) because the classics just can’t be beat.  i was craving something sweet, salty, and simple and this hit the spot x10000. consider this is your reminder to eat what the heck you want, because ignoring our cravings never solved anything <333333

node.text:
this week has been long and it’s only monday 💀 nothing a batch of muffins in the oven (and an extra handful of chocolate chunks eaten on the side) can’t fix! i love these breakfast muffins for a sweet and salty start to my day that will actually keep me full 🤪 anyone else team sweet > team savory when it comes to breakfast? i’m usually savory everythingggg but breakfast is an exception 😙

almond butter breakfast muffins

set oven to 350 and line a muffin tin with liners.

in a small bowl whisk together:

- 1 small mashed banana
- 1 egg
- 1/3 cup non-dairy milk
- 1/3 cup almond butter (can sub any nut butter)
- splash of vanilla

in a separate bowl whisk together:

- 1 cup almomd flour
- 1/2 cup oat flour
- dash of sea salt
- dash of cinnamon

add the wet to dry and mix until well-combined. stir through chocolate of choice (if using) and scoop batter into muffin liners. bake for about 20-25 minutes!
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
a weekend spent mostly in my own company. a weekend of self love and healing and rest. a weekend of kind words spoken to my body in a bathing suit. a weekend of breathing through bad thoughts and replacing them with better ones. a weekend saturated in sun and supplemented with sweets (recipe for that last slide coming soon!). a weekend at home, where i feel my roots grounding me. a weekend- a good one. i’m feeling extra blessed to call this life mine lately ♥️ hope sunday treats you well friends! xx

node.text:
a treat for you, from the archives 😚 this loaf is sweet and salty with the fluffiest texture! plus i find it keeps me full and satisfied thanks to our bestie miss almond butter 🙆🏻‍♀️ if you haven’t had the chance to make this one yet, this is a sign 👀

vanilla almond butter loaf

set oven to 350F and grease a loaf pan. in a mixing bowl combine:

- 3 eggs
- 1/2 cup almond milk
- 1/2 cup coconut sugar
- 1/4 cup creamy salted almond butter
- 1/4 cup maple syrup
- splash of vanilla

mix until uniform and then add:

- 1 cup almond flour
- 1 cup oat flour
- pinch of baking powder
- pinch of sea salt

combine until smooth then pour batter into the loaf pan. bake for 45-50 minutes and let cool completely before icing. for the icing i just combined 1 single serve (5.3oz) container of plain coconut yogurt with 1 tbsp each of coconut sugar and maple syrup. pour over loaf and place in fridge to set for an hour before slicing

node.text:
a soft reminder that you are in charge of your own happiness. you have control over your narrative. if something isn’t serving you, you have the power to step away. and if you don’t, at the very least you have the power to change how you react.

these points apply to our roles as conscious consumers online. one of the luxuries of controlling our own social media presence and landscape is that we can follow and un follow new accounts any time we want to- nothing is binding! immerse yourself in spaces that make you feel supported, whole, and seen. ones that contribute to a strong headspace, ones that give you hope for goals you’re working toward and a sense of gratitude for ones you’ve accomplished. 

in light of both the DM (second slide) i received recently and the stories i shared yesterday about food mongering (slides 3-5), i was reminded that social media can be toxic. but i know firsthand it can also be positive and powerful. the way we choose to use this tool is up to us. we can continue following and exposing ourselves to content that is harmful to us because we’re conditioned to believe it’s healthy. OR we can act on behalf of our own healing journeys and cultivate a space where we can grow. oh, and we can call out BS when we see it (hi health coaches with no credentials 👋)!

if you follow accounts that make you feel bad— stop. if you follow accounts that trigger harmful thoughts or behaviors— stop. in order to use online communities to heal, grow, and improve ourselves, we must be conscious consumers. it’s okay to walk away in the name of self-love. in fact, i highly, highly recommend it xxxxx

node.text:
sunday 🤌 swipe for free therapy hehe. hope this weekend was a good one! i worked a bit, rested a lot, and ate some of my favorite foods 🙆🏻‍♀️ leaving this classic chocolate chip cookie recipe below for you to make for dessert tonight 🍪🍪🍪🍪🍪 

classic chocolate chip cookies

* 1/3 cup vegan butter, softened
* 1/2 cup coconut sugar 
* 1 egg (can try a flax egg though i haven’t myself)!
* splash of vanilla 
* 1 cup almond flour 
* 2 tbsp oat flour (can use any gluten-free flour)
* pinch of baking powder and sea salt 
* chocolate chips of choice

set oven to 350 and grease a cookie sheet. in a  bowl using a hand mixer, beat butter and  coconut sugar. add in egg and vanilla and bear again until well combined. in a separate bowl, mix together flour, baking powder, and salt. add the dry ingredients to the wet and mix until well combined. stir in chocolate of choice. use a cookie scoop to drop dough onto the sheet and bake for about 10-12 minutes, or until golden brown. 
.
.
.

node.text:
introduciiiiing a *NEW* type of swipe to build post! lol. things are getting wild here at HRHQ 😀 i had this little tutorial saved in my camera roll and thought it deserved a home here on my feed. you’re looking at my favorite vegan sandwich at the moment. listen to the bread crunch!!!! 🤌 definitley my go-to lunch for most wfh days.

no true recipe here. grab your favorite bread, hummus, prepared tofu (or any other protein of choice), and greens. then just assemble as shown. i have a reel coming next week with how i prepare my tofu/tempeh so watch out for that 🤠 

oh and remember, carbs are our friends <333333

#healthyfood #healthy #foodie #cleaneats #foodblogger #veganfood #carbs #sandwich #glutenfree #wellness #fitness #healthyinspo #healthylife #healthymeals #plantpower #thenewhealth #mbg #food52grams #thefeedfeed #tofu #hummus #swipetobuild #kale
